body:
Hi All,
I recently had a lot of trouble using some features of ShaderProgram class.
According to the javadoc: 

``` java
/** Sets the uniform with the given name. Throws an IllegalArgumentException in case it is not called in between a
     * {@link #begin()}/{@link #end()} block.
     * 
     * @param name the name of the uniform
     * @param values x and y as the first and second values respectively */
    public void setUniformf (String name, Vector2 values) {
        setUniformf(name, values.x, values.y);
    }

```

But if I try to execute the following code:

``` java
@Override
    public void render() {
        Gdx.gl.glClearColor(0.8f, 0.8f, 0.8f, 1.0f);
        Gdx.gl.glClear(GL20.GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);

        viewport.update(Gdx.graphics.getWidth(), Gdx.graphics.getHeight());
        batch.setProjectionMatrix(camera.combined);

        fontShader.setUniformf("u_glow", GLOW);
        fontShader.setUniformf("u_outline", OUTLINE);

        batch.begin();



        fontShader.setUniformf("u_glowColor", GLOW_COLOR);
        fontShader.setUniformf("u_outlineColor", OUTLINE_COLOR);

        fontShader.setUniformi("u_enableGlow", 0);
        fontShader.setUniformi("u_enableOutline", 0);
        font.draw(batch, " No effects", 20.0f, VIRTUAL_HEIGHT - 50.0f);
        batch.flush();

        fontShader.setUniformi("u_enableGlow", 0);
        fontShader.setUniformi("u_enableOutline", 1);
        font.draw(batch, "Just outline", 20.0f, VIRTUAL_HEIGHT - 200.0f);
        batch.flush();

        fontShader.setUniformi("u_enableGlow", 1);
        fontShader.setUniformi("u_enableOutline", 0);
        font.draw(batch, "Just glow", 20.0f, VIRTUAL_HEIGHT - 350.0f);
        batch.flush();

        fontShader.setUniformi("u_enableGlow", 1);
        fontShader.setUniformi("u_enableOutline", 1);
        font.draw(batch, "Outline and glow", 20.0f, VIRTUAL_HEIGHT - 500.0f);
        batch.flush();

        batch.end();
    }

```

no exception is thrown!! I have spent a lot of time looking at that trying to understand why the shader didn't works. 

I think it's a bug, let me know your view.

Thanks!
Daniele.
